    </custom_item>

    <custom_item>
      type        : CMD_EXEC
      description : "4.3.1.6 Ensure snapp is not installed"
      info        : "snapp provides a perl-based interface to do the initial network configuration of an IBM RISC System/6000, from a Palm Pilot, via RS232C.

Systems running as logical partitions will not have access to an RS232C port, network configuration is performed either via NIM or through the virtual terminal provided by the Hardware Management Console. The snapp service is therefore not required and should be removed to reduce the attack surface of the system."
      solution    : "Remove the software

installp -u bos.net.snapp"
      reference   : "800-171|3.4.2,800-171|3.4.6,800-171|3.4.7,800-171r3|03.04.02,800-171r3|03.04.06,800-53|CM-6,800-53|CM-7,800-53r5|CM-6,800-53r5|CM-7,CSCv7|9.2,CSCv8|4.8,CSF|PR.IP-1,CSF|PR.PT-3,CSF2.0|DE.CM-09,CSF2.0|PR.PS-01,GDPR|32.1.b,HIPAA|164.306(a)(1),ISO-27001-2022|A.8.9,ITSG-33|CM-6,ITSG-33|CM-7,LEVEL|1A,NIAv2|SS15a,PCI-DSSv3.2.1|2.2.2,SWIFT-CSCv1|2.3"
      see_also    : "https://workbench.cisecurity.org/benchmarks/22751"
      cmd         : "/usr/bin/lslpp -Lcq bos.net.snapp"
      expect      : "[\\s]*not[\\s]+installed\\.[\\s]*$"
